Previous page

  3. DIVElink smart watches

  4. Does this smart watch compatible with iphone/android phone?

    Yes, DIVElink smart watches 100% compatible with iphone and Android phone, Huawei smart phone

    A smartwatch can work without a smartphone?

    Yes.

    Without Bluetooth connection to your phone, the smartwatch can still be used as an independent watch to check the time, calories burned, counting steps, distance run, etc. There’s just no way to see more history and no way to get notifications from your cellphone.

    Can you make phone calls on a smartwatch?

    Yes. This is a Bluetooth smartwatch, first download the App to your smartphone then connect.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

  • Amazon Customer
    5.0 out of 5 stars Value for price
    Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    I bought this watch since my dietician suggested I keep track and try to set a daily goal of steps taken daily since I didn't really want or need much else, I wanted to spend less money than on a Fitbit. This fit the bill, does what I want, and is pretty simple to use. The watchface is pretty large, but I think you can tell that in the listing.
    I will say the directions that came in the box has quite a small font- but I downloaded a copy off the internet and could magnify them.
    The setup and use was pretty easy to get used to and the battery life seems to last quite a while between charging. I have not had to charge it the second time and have only had it a week and it is still at 71%.
    You can choose a background for the home screen (which is the actual time face) and I think it's cute!
    The band is a bit like rubber/plastic, a bit stiff, but soft. Seems to need a bit of breaking in for pliability. I cannot imagine wantinh to wear it to bed, but it says it has "sleep tracking".
    So to me, this piece works for what I want it to do, for a valid price point, and doesn't look too bad!
